Title: The Vanishing of Will Byers
Description: On his way home from a friend's house, young Will Byers mysteriously disappears. As the town of Hawkins, Indiana, unravels the mystery, they uncover a series of extraordinary events and a government conspiracy.

Title: The Weirdo on Maple Street
Description: As the search for Will continues, Mike, Dustin, and Lucas stumble upon a girl with telekinetic powers named Eleven. Meanwhile, Joyce receives a series of mysterious phone calls.

Title: Holly, Jolly
Description: While Joyce tries to make contact with Will, Chief Hopper questions an anxious Joyce about an unsettling phone call. Meanwhile, the boys use Eleven's powers to find Will.

Title: The Body
Description: Refusing to believe Will is dead, Joyce tries to connect with him. The boys give Eleven a makeover. Nancy and Jonathan form an unlikely alliance.

Title: The Flea and the Acrobat
Description: Hopper breaks into the lab while Nancy and Jonathan confront the force that took Will. The boys ask Mr. Clarke how to travel to another dimension.

Title: The Monster
Description: A frantic Jonathan looks for Nancy in the darkness, but Steve's looking for her too. Hopper and Joyce uncover the truth about the lab's experiments.

Title: The Bathtub
Description: Eleven struggles to reach Will, while Lucas warns his friends about the government's plans. Nancy and Jonathan show the police what Jonathan caught on camera.

Title: The Upside Down
Description: Dr. Brenner holds Hopper and Joyce for questioning while the boys wait with Eleven in the gym. Back at Will's, Nancy and Jonathan prepare for battle.
